question: Question_07_(a)
statement:
For each subset of $\mathbb{R}$ give its supremum, maximum, infimum, and
minimum if they exist. If they do not exist write \emph{``none''}. You
do not need to justify your answers.

\begin{longtable}[c]{@{}lllll@{}}
the sets & sup & max & inf & min\\

$\{x\in\mathbb{R}\quad\textrm{s.t.}\quad{}2\leq{x}<\pi\}$ & & & &\\
$\{x\in\mathbb{Q}\quad\textrm{s.t.}\quad{}x\geq0\quad\textrm{and}\quad{}x^2\leq5\}$
& & & &\\
$\{x\in\mathbb{Z}\quad\textrm{s.t.}\quad{}x^2\geq4\}$ & & & &\\
$\bigcup_{n=1}^\infty\left[\frac{1}{n},n^2+1\right]$ & & & &\\
\end{longtable}
